<div class="page-content">

<!-- ENGLISH (default, all languages except French) -->
<div id="disc-en">
  <h1>Disclosure</h1>
  <p>This page explains how AplusZ works, how it stays free, and how it handles your data. We keep it plain and honest.</p>

  <h2>Affiliate &amp; partner links</h2>
  <p>AplusZ may link to our own other projects and partner services; some links are affiliated and may earn us a commission at no extra cost to you.</p>
  <p>When you tap a "Book" button, we send you to a travel partner (for example, flight search via our travel partners). If you book there, we may receive a small commission. The price you pay is the same whether or not you use our link.</p>

  <h2>How AplusZ stays free</h2>
  <p>AplusZ is free to use, with unlimited searches and no signup. The app is funded by affiliate commissions and by optional paid plans (Pro and Pro+). This lets the core service stay free for everyone.</p>

  <h2>What we store on your device</h2>
  <p>AplusZ saves a few things in your browser's local storage so the app works for you: your two chosen cities, your saved routes and reminders, your language and theme, and (if you upgrade) your plan status. This data lives on your device. We do not sell it and we do not use third-party advertising or tracking cookies.</p>

  <h2>No tracking</h2>
  <p>AplusZ does not run third-party analytics or advertising trackers. We do not build a profile of you across the web.</p>

  <h2>Your control</h2>
  <p>You can clear AplusZ's stored data at any time by clearing your browser's site data. The app keeps working � it simply forgets your saved cities and preferences.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions about this disclosure? Email <a href="mailto:dagrang@gmail.com">dagrang@gmail.com</a>. For full legal terms and the GDPR privacy policy, see the <a href="../legal/index.html">Legal</a> page.</p>

  <p class="updated">Last updated: May 2026</p>
</div>

